TOPICS COVERED (SUPERVISED MACHINE LEARNING – INTRODUCTION & MODEL BUILDING)
Introduction to Supervised Machine Learning

The training session began with an introduction to Supervised Machine Learning, one of the most widely used categories of Machine Learning. Learned that supervised learning is a technique in which a model is trained using labeled data, where both the input features and the corresponding target outputs are already known. The trainer explained that the model learns the relationship between input variables and output labels, enabling it to make accurate predictions on unseen data.

Discussed several real-world applications of supervised learning, including spam email detection, house price prediction, disease diagnosis, student performance prediction, loan approval systems, and fraud detection.

